               <head>Qasidah on Badr combatants</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary />
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85109396 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh91002715 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh87000556 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85010921" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Or_16846-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>An untitled poem enumerating and praising each of Aṣḥāb-i Badr, the Muslim warriors who fought in the Battle of <placeName>Badr</placeName>. The author gives his name as <persName key="person_f7447" role="aut">Naṣr Allāh</persName>. This manuscript is of special interest as having been copied, illuminated and bound in Afghanistan in the early 14th/20th century.
                        </p>
                        <p>Begins:
Basmala... Ḥamd-i bīḥadd shud sazā-yi Ḥaẓrat-i Parvardgār/kaz Rasūlān Aḥmad-i Mukhtār-rā kard ikhtiyār,
Khāliq-i mulk va malak falak falak jinn va bashar/‘ulvī u suflī u najm u khāk u bād u āb u nār
</p>
                        <p>Ends:
Bār Ilāha sāmi‘an va qāriyan va kātiban/jumla-gī-rā bakhsh u bar rūshān gunāh-i-shān mayār,
Mā agarchi ummatīm az muznibīn u ākhirīn/dast-i mā va dāman-i aṣḥāb-i ū Rūz-i Shumār
</p>
                        <p>Colophon, f. 12v. Produced for <persName key="person_f7069" role="pat">ʿĀlījāh Mīrzā Brigadier Muḥammad Ḥusayn Khān</persName>. Dated 1319/1901-2. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Good nasta‘līq. 10 lines. Text frames: blue; blue, black, gold. Interlinear gilding throughout. Illuminated headpiece of good quality, 1v. 12 folios, plus 14 blank. 200 x 122 mm.; text area 136 x 80 mm. Original good Afghan red leather covers with blind impressed ornamentation at front and back. </p>
                        <p>Purchased from Bonhams (24 November 2011, part of Lot 186). </p>
                     </note>
